<h2>Guidelines</h2>
<h3>Lists for lists</h3>
<p>List elements are meant for content that is a list. It's tempting to overuse these for layout, so take time to think about some better alternatives to list elements that could be used. One common alternative for navigation is this:</p>
<code-sample>
  <!-- Better -->
  <nav>
    <a href="">Link</a>
    <a href="">Link</a>
    <a href="">Link</a>
  </nav>

  <!-- Bad habit -->
  <ul type="none">
    <li class="inline"><a href="">Link</a></li>
    <li class="inline"><a href="">Link</a></li>
    <li class="inline"><a href="">Link</a></li>
  </ul>
</code-sample>
<h3>Accessibility</h3>
<p>Use the correct list parent elements for your use case, i.e. <code>ol</code> when the list order is meaningful and <code>ul</code> when it isn't.</p>
